5. ops.vx - Operator Overloading Contracts â€‹

rust
// Arithmetic
contract Add { op+(rhs: Self): Self; }
contract Sub { op-(rhs: Self): Self; }
contract Mul { op*(rhs: Self): Self; }
contract Div { op/(rhs: Self): Self; }
contract Mod { op%(rhs: Self): Self; }
contract Neg { op-(): Self; }

// Bitwise
contract BitAnd { op&(rhs: Self): Self; }
contract BitOr  { op|(rhs: Self): Self; }
contract BitXor { op^(rhs: Self): Self; }
contract BitNot { op~(): Self; }
contract Shl    { op<<(rhs: i32): Self; }
contract Shr    { op>>(rhs: i32): Self; }

// Comparison
contract Eq  { op==(rhs: Self): bool; op!=(rhs: Self): bool; }
contract Ord { op<(rhs: Self): bool; op>(rhs: Self): bool;
               op<=(rhs: Self): bool; op>=(rhs: Self): bool; }
contract Not { op!(): bool; }

// Compound Assignment
contract AddAssign { op+=(rhs: Self); }
contract SubAssign { op-=(rhs: Self); }
contract MulAssign { op*=(rhs: Self); }
contract DivAssign { op/=(rhs: Self); }
contract ModAssign { op%=(rhs: Self); }

// Index
contract Index    { type Output; op[](index: i32): Output; }
contract IndexMut { op[]=(index: i32, value: Self); }

// Advanced
contract Pow           { op**(exp: i32): Self; }
contract PreInc        { op++(): Self; }
contract PostInc       { op++(): Self; }
contract PreDec        { op--(): Self; }
contract PostDec       { op--(): Self; }
contract Range         { op..(end: Self): Range<Self>; }
contract RangeInclusive{ op..=(end: Self): RangeInclusive<Self>; }
contract NullCoalesce  { op??(fallback: Self): Self; }

Null Safety Operators â€‹

OperatorContractDescriptionExample
??NullCoalesceReturns left if not nil, otherwise rightx ?? default
?.(built-in)Optional chaining - returns nil if niluser?.name
!>(built-in)Error rescue - handle error inlineop() !> |e| val

Null Coalesce (??): Provides default value when left operand is nil.

rust
let name = user.nickname ?? user.username ?? "Guest";
let count = map.get("key") ?? 0;

Optional Chaining (?.): Safely access members of potentially nil values.

rust
let city = user?.address?.city;  // Returns nil if user or address is nil
let len = str?.len();            // Returns nil if str is nil

Error Rescue (!>): Handle Result errors inline without match expressions.

rust
let data = parse(text) !> |e| default_data;
let value = fetch(url) !> handle_error;

See Error_rescue_operator.spec.md for full !> specification.

Durum: âœ… Aktif kullanÄ±mda
Not: Compound assignment ve index operators henÃ¼z tam implement deÄŸil

Slice<T> â€‹

Kaynak: vex-compiler/src/codegen_ast/builtins/slice.rs, vex-runtime/c/src/collections/vex_slice.c

Slice, sabit boyutlu array'lere veya variadic parametrelere dinamik bir view saÄŸlar. Variadic fonksiyonlar (...T) otomatik olarak Slice<T> olarak derlenir.

Runtime Struct:

c

    void *data;      // Pointer to array data
    size_t len;      // Number of elements
    size_t elem_size; // Size of each element in bytes

Builtin Fonksiyonlar:

FonksiyonÄ°mzaAÃ§Ä±klamaDurum
vex_slice_new(ptr, len, size): SliceCreate slice from raw memoryâœ…

Method Syntax (Variadic Parameters):

rust
fn sum(nums: ...i32): i32 {
    let! total = 0;
    
    // Method calls on slice
    let count = nums.len();        // Get count
    let first = nums.get(0);       // Get by index
    let empty = nums.is_empty();   // Check empty
    
    // For-in iteration
    for n in nums {
        total = total + n;
    }
    
    return total;
}

// Usage
let result = sum(1, 2, 3, 4, 5);  // 15
let empty_result = sum();          // 0
